<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2887] --with-openssl configure flag is ignored</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2887</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;configure&lt;/tt&gt; script offers a &lt;tt&gt;--with-openssl&lt;/tt&gt; option:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;  --with-openssl=DIR      root of the OpenSSL directory
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, this doesn&apos;t appear to be respected by the C++ build.  (There is one nested reference to &lt;tt&gt;AX_CHECK_OPENSSL&lt;/tt&gt; within part of the D language configuration.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;--with-openssl&lt;/tt&gt; is useful when building Thrift on OS X because the base system&apos;s SSL libraries are insufficient.  See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2515&quot; title=&quot;TLS Method error during make&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-2515&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-2515&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
